none: Mŏdŏllyŏng is the first collection of poems from the later years of Japanese occupation by Chŏng Hun (1911- ), a poet of contemporary and traditional poems (a.k.a. sijo). Number of poems in this collection delicately illustrates the native culture and sentiment. Cover design and illustrations by Yi Tong-hun.
